---
title: "Request Flow — Hot Path"
---
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Adapter as Channel Adapter<br/>(Slack / Discord / CLI / Co-Pilot)
    participant API as Central API
    participant Auth as Auth + Entitlement
    participant Ctx as Context Engine
    participant Det as Skill Detection
    participant Router as Router
    participant LLM as LLM Backend<br/>(Claude / Codex)
    participant RAG as Canon + RAG
    participant Mem as User Memory
    participant Kafka as Kafka<br/>(async)

    User ->> Adapter: Message
    Adapter ->> Adapter: Normalize message<br/>+ inject project context<br/>(.flox/ detection)

    Adapter ->> API: POST /chat (normalized msg)
    
    API ->> Auth: Validate token
    Auth -->> API: Tier: pro, rate: OK

    API ->> Ctx: Build context
    Ctx ->> Mem: Load user memory (Tier 1)
    Mem -->> Ctx: Past issues, skill level,<br/>preferred tools
    
    Ctx ->> Ctx: Check cross-channel<br/>session (Flink output)

    API ->> Det: Detect skills
    Det ->> Det: Manifest has terraform + aws
    Det -->> API: Load skill:terraform (primary)<br/>+ skill:aws (secondary)

    API ->> Router: Classify intent
    Router ->> Router: "terraform plan failing"<br/>→ DIAGNOSTIC → Claude

    Router ->> RAG: Query canon
    RAG -->> Router: Top-k relevant chunks<br/>+ skill-specific Q&A

    Router ->> LLM: Prompt with:<br/>System + User Memory + RAG<br/>+ skill:terraform (full)<br/>+ skill:aws (summary)<br/>+ manifest context

    LLM -->> Router: Response

    Router -->> API: Response + confidence score
    API -->> Adapter: Formatted response + vote buttons
    Adapter -->> User: Platform-native rendering

    Note over Adapter,Kafka: Async side effects (after response sent)
    
    Adapter -) Kafka: Publish to .inbound
    API -) Kafka: Publish response to .outbound
    API -) Kafka: Publish context to .context

    Note over User,Adapter: User votes
    User ->> Adapter: 👍 Helpful
    Adapter -) Kafka: Publish to .votes
